er-widgets/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 29 Jul 2015 07:55:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=667104";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:369:"Need to translate footer texts or sliders but strings do not appear for translation? First check if any of those strings are set by the theme&#8217;s WPML XML config file on WPML &#62; Translation Management &#62; Multilingual Content Setup screen under section &#8216;Admin Strings to Translate&#8217;. If the whole section is missing or strings you&#8217;re [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"srdjan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5405:"<p>Need to translate footer texts or sliders but strings do not appear for translation?</p>\n<p>First check if any of those strings are set by the theme&#8217;s WPML XML config file on <em>WPML &gt; Translation Management &gt; Multilingual Content Setup</em> screen under section &#8216;Admin Strings to Translate&#8217;.</p>\n<div id="attachment_667113" style="width: 160px" class="wp-caption alignleft"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/wpprorealestate6wpml-2015-07-24-16-20-22.png"><img class="wp-image-667113 size-thumbnail" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/wpprorealestate6wpml-2015-07-24-16-20-22-150x77.png" alt="Theme slider" width="150" height="77" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Theme slider</p></div>\n<div id="attachment_667153" style="width: 160px" class="wp-caption alignleft"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Translation-Management-----beckettwpml-----WordPress-2015-07-27-12-23-31.png"><img class="wp-image-667153 size-thumbnail" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Translation-Management-----beckettwpml-----WordPress-2015-07-27-12-23-31-150x85.png" alt="Translation Management" width="150" height="85" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Multilingual Content Setup</p></div>\n<div style="clear: both"></div>\n<p>If the whole section is missing or strings you&#8217;re looking for are not there &#8211; no worries!</p>\n<h2>Find and translate theme options</h2>\n<p>Using WPML String Translation, you can translate any option used on your site. Just mark them as translatable on <em>WPML &gt; String Translation &gt; Translate texts in admin screens</em>.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-24-16-22-23.png"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-667120" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-24-16-22-23-150x89.png" alt="String Translation" width="150" height="89" /></a></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll have to find the right option. Usually theme options are listed somewhere below &#8216;theme_mods_{themename}&#8217;. We looked for <em>WP Real Estate Pro</em> theme options and found them named &#8216;WP Pro Real Estate 6_options&#8217;.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-27-12-13-31.png"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-667136" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-27-12-13-31-150x100.png" alt="String Translation" width="150" height="100" /></a></p>\n<p>Under that tree we can find the sliders stored under name &#8216;ct_flex_slider&#8217;. We marked each existing slide title as translatable.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-24-16-26-19.png"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-667138" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-24-16-26-19-150x73.png" alt="String Translation" width="150" height="73" /></a></p>\n<p>After saving preferences, slide titles will appear on <em>WPML &gt; String Translation</em> screen.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-24-16-29-53.png"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-667142" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/String-Translation-----wpprorealestate6wpml-----WordPress-2015-07-24-16-29-53-150x48.png" alt="String Translation" width="150" height="48" /></a></p>\n<p>Translate titles and see slides translated on frontend.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Spanish-wpprorealestate6wpml-2015-07-24-16-30-55.png"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-667146" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Spanish-wpprorealestate6wpml-2015-07-24-16-30-55-150x80.png" alt="&#091;Spanish&#093; wpprorealestate6&amp;wpml 2015-07-24 16-30-55" width="150" height="80" /></a></p>\n<p>We hope it was not too complicated. You can use this approach to translate any other theme option if necessary. For example, <strong>custom Widgets</strong> can be usually found under options named like &#8216;widget_{widget_name}&#8217;.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4768lykGwK8:EIwUZ53BvkU:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4768lykGwK8:EIwUZ53BvkU:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4768lykGwK8:EIwUZ53BvkU:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4768lykGwK8:EIwUZ53BvkU:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=4768lykGwK8:EIwUZ53BvkU:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=4768lykGwK8:EIwUZ53BvkU:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/4768lykGwK8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"https://wpml.org/2015/07/translating-theme-options-sliders-footer-widgets/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://wpml.org/2015/07/translating-theme-options-sliders-footer-widgets/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"WooCommerce Multilingual and WooCommerce Bookings";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/U7SmHobg1GU/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"https://wpml.org/2015/07/woocommerce-multilingual-and-woocommerce-bookings/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 23 Jul 2015 10:40:27 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:22:"Compatibility Bulletin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=603719";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:386:"WooCommerce Bookings is an extension that allows you to sell time- or date-based bookings. Bookings are organized as a new WooCommerce product type called ‘bookable products’. Translating bookable products If you run a multilingual e-commerce site, you may need to translate the bookable products into other languages. WooCommerce Multilingual helps you do just that, when [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Mihai";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10219:"<p>WooCommerce Bookings is an extension that allows you to sell time- or date-based bookings. Bookings are organized as a new WooCommerce product type called ‘bookable products’.</p>\n<h2>Translating bookable products</h2>\n<p>If you run a multilingual e-commerce site, you may need to translate the bookable products into other languages. WooCommerce Multilingual helps you do just that, when your site also runs WPML and the required addons.</p>\n<h3>Using WooCommerce Multilingual products translation</h3>\n<p>We recommend translating bookable products with the products-translation screen in the WooCommerce Multilingual plugin.</p>\n<div id="attachment_603736" style="width: 710px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image00.png"><img class="wp-image-603736 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image00.png" alt="Translating bookable products using the products translation screen" width="700" height="377" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating bookable products using the products translation screen</p></div>\n<p>On this screen, you can translate the product attributes in the same way you translate all the other product types.</p>\n<h4>Translating WooCommerce Booking Resources</h4>\n<p>Sometimes bookings require additional items. For example, if you book a tennis court, you may need to borrow rackets. These rackets will be ‘resources’.</p>\n<p>When customers book, they can select to include ‘resources’. Customers can select resources when they add products to the cart. The store can charge additional money when including resources with products.</p>\n<p>When resources are being used, they can be translated from the products-translation interface, on the same screen as other product types and for all languages in one place.</p>\n<div id="attachment_603743" style="width: 633px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image07.png"><img class="wp-image-603743 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image07.png" alt="Translating WooCommerce Booking resources " width="623" height="362" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating WooCommerce Booking resources</p></div>\n<h4>Translating WooCommerce Booking Persons</h4>\n<p>In some cases, bookings are made for a specific number of persons. The cost depends on the number and type of persons. For instance, when you purchase a ticket for a show, you need to enter the number of persons and whether they are an adult or a child, etc.</p>\n<p>In a situation like this, you can translate the labels and the descriptions for the person types using the same products-translation screen.</p>\n<div id="attachment_603737" style="width: 598px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image01.png"><img class="wp-image-603737 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image01.png" alt="Translating persons labels and descriptions" width="588" height="437" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating persons labels and descriptions</p></div>\n<h3>Using WooCommerce native products editor</h3>\n<p>Another way in which you can translate bookable products is using the standard WooCommerce products editor. You need to enable this mode explicitly from the WooCommerce Multilingual general settings page.</p>\n<p>This will allow you to translate the product elements, but less flexibly than using the WooCommerce Multilingual products-translation screen, since you have to edit one product translation at a time.</p>\n<div id="attachment_603738" style="width: 710px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image02.png"><img class="wp-image-603738 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image02.png" alt="Translating persons labels using the WooCommerce products editor" width="700" height="453" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Translating persons labels using the WooCommerce products editor</p></div>\n<h2>Using multiple currencies for bookable products</h2>\n<p>Using WooCommerce Multilingual you can also sell your bookable products in different currencies. First, you need to enable the multi-currency mode from the general settings and then you can add custom currencies. More about this is covered on the <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/multi-currency-support-woocommerce/">Multi-currency support for WooCommerce</a> documentation page.</p>\n<h3>Fixed exchange rate</h3>\n<p>There are two ways in which you can determine the prices for custom currencies. By default, the prices are calculated based on the exchange rate that you enter when adding a new currency, but they are also affected by the other configuration settings: number of decimals, rounding, etc. When you update the exchange rate for a currency, all prices update accordingly.</p>\n<p>On the front end, the clients will be able to switch to the prices in other currencies by using the currency selector, as in the image below.</p>\n<div id="attachment_603739" style="width: 651px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image03.png"><img class="wp-image-603739 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image03.png" alt="A currency switcher on a product page" width="641" height="526" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">A currency switcher on a product page</p></div>\n<p>More advanced options are also available. For example, you can enable a different currency for each language, set it as the default currency that the users would see when switching to that language, but also exclude other currencies so there’s only one currency for each language.</p>\n<h3>Custom prices in different currencies</h3>\n<p>The other way to set the prices in the secondary currencies is by enabling the ‘manual’ pricing mode. You can do this for each individual bookable product under the ‘Costs’ tab. When this option is enabled, a series of fields for entering the prices in the secondary currencies is displayed.</p>\n<div id="attachment_603741" style="width: 709px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image05.png"><img class="wp-image-603741 " src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image05.png" alt="Adding custom prices in the secondary currencies" width="699" height="441" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Adding custom prices in the secondary currencies</p></div>\n<p>So, in this case, the prices in the secondary currencies are being set explicitly and not determined automatically based on the exchange rate. Changing the exchange rate for a currency will not affect these prices.</p>\n<p>Similar fields for custom prices show up on the Persons tab, if enabled, and on the Resources tab.</p>\n<div id="attachment_603740" style="width: 670px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image04.png"><img class="wp-image-603740" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image04.png" alt="Adding costs in the secondary currencies for persons" width="660" height="396" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Adding costs in the secondary currencies for persons</p></div>\n<div id="attachment_603742" style="width: 670px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image06.png"><img class="wp-image-603742 size-full" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/image06.png" alt="Adding costs in the secondary currencies for resources " width="660" height="396" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Adding costs in the secondary currencies for resources</p></div>\n<h2>Download and setup</h2>\n<p>WooCommerce Bookings is a commercial extension available on the <a href="http://www.woothemes.com/products/woocommerce-bookings/">WooThemes extensions catalog</a>. It requires WooCommerce, which is a free plugin available in the WordPress plugins directory.</p>\n<p>WooCommerce Multilingual is also a WooCommerce extension. It’s a glue plugin for WooCommerce and WPML and is also available for download on the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/">WordPress plugins directory</a>.</p>\n<p>After installing WooCommerce Multilingual on an existing WooCommerce site with bookable products, further steps are needed in order to have a fully set-up multilingual shop. They are described on the <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/#2">WooCommerce Multilingual main documentation page</a>.</p>\n<h2>Your feedback</h2>\n<p>WooCommerce Multilingual includes compatibility with a wide range of WooCommerce extensions. We’re actively working on covering as many of these extensions as possible, while also including other functionalities, like multi-currency mode.</p>\n<p>WooCommerce Bookings is the most recent extension we have covered and added complete support for in <a href="https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/woocommerce-multilingual.3.6.5.zip">WooCommerce Multilingual 3.6.5</a>. We’d love to hear your feedback on your experience with WooCommerce Bookings and WooCommerce Multilingual.</p>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=U7SmHobg1GU:oSrOJ1yfoBQ:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=U7SmHobg1GU:oSrOJ1yfoBQ:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=U7SmHobg1GU:oSrOJ1yfoBQ:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=U7SmHobg1GU:oSrOJ1yfoBQ:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=U7SmHobg1GU:oSrOJ1yfoBQ:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=U7SmHobg1GU: